main event: An unidentified object was observed in Los Angeles, California on 16 May 1956, believed to be Venus.
interesting points: The object was described as delta-shaped and flashing, resembling a pea., The observers thought the object was stationary and compared it to a star., The sighting lasted for approximately 20 minutes., The conclusion identified the object as most likely being the planet Venus., There were six other observers present during the sighting.
witness description: engineer for Bendix Co. and six others
